Detailed Description

cvmx_gser::_lane_p::_mode_1

These are the RAW PCS lane settings mode 1 registers. There is one register per 4 lanes, (0..3) per GSER per GSER_LMODE_E value (0..11). Only one entry is used at any given time in a given GSER lane - the one selected by the corresponding GSER()_LANE_MODE[LMODE]. These registers are reset by hardware only during chip cold reset. The values of the CSR fields in these registers do not change during chip warm or soft resets.
